      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and blind-bake the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold {{unsalted-butter}} (for the pastry) into the {{plain-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} until the mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs. Mix in the egg yolk and 2 tablespoons of cold water until the dough just comes together. Chill for 20 minutes. Roll out and line a 23 cm tart tin. Prick the base, line with baking paper, and fill with baking beans. Blind-bake at 190°C fan for 15 minutes. Remove the beans and paper and bake for a further 5 to 8 minutes until the pastry is dry and lightly golden. Cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill with jam and banana",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spread the {{raspberry-jam}} over the base of the cooled pastry case. Arrange the sliced {{bananas}} over the jam.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and pour the custard",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk the {{cornflour}} and {{caster-sugar}} with 4 tablespoons of the {{whole-milk}} to a smooth paste. Bring the remaining milk to a simmer in a saucepan. Pour the hot milk onto the cornflour paste, whisking constantly, then return to the pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring continuously, for 3 to 4 minutes until thick. Remove from the heat and stir in the {{vanilla-extract}} and {{unsalted-butter}} (for the custard). Pour immediately over the banana in the pastry case.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Chill and finish",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Leave the tart to cool for 20 minutes, then refrigerate for at least 2 hours until the custard is fully set. Before serving, scatter the {{desiccated-coconut}} over the top and arrange the halved {{glace-cherries}} decoratively.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
